From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jiaxing Hu <huhuvmb88@outlook.com>
Date: Mon, 7 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +1200
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: rk3568: rock-3b: enable the NPU

Enable the RKNPU + its IOMMU on the Radxa ROCK 3B and pin vdd_npu on so\nthe first NPU power-domain enable does not -ETIMEDOUT. UNTESTED on real\nhardware yet -- pending ROCK 3B validation.

Signed-off-by: Jiaxing Hu <huhuvmb88@outlook.com>
---
diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3568-rock-3b.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3568-rock-3b.dts
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3568-rock-3b.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3568-rock-3b.dts
@@ -787,3 +787,19 @@
 		remote-endpoint = <&hdmi_in_vp0>;
 	};
 };
+
+&rknpu {
+	status = "okay";
+};
+
+&rknpu_mmu {
+	status = "okay";
+};
+
+&vdd_npu {
+	/*
+	 * Claim vdd_npu early: without a consumer the regulator core disables
+	 * DCDC_REG4 after boot, so the first NPU power-domain enable -ETIMEDOUTs.
+	 */
+	regulator-always-on;
+};
--
2.43.0
